## 1. Java Concepts & Code Structure (Theory)

Java language-la oru program ezhuthumpothu, basic-ah sila rules and structures follow pannanum. Athoda theory itho:

### A. Imports (Imports Enral Enna?)
Namma program-oda starting-la munu imports ezhuthi irupom:
```java
import java.util.Scanner;
import java.util.regex.Matcher;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;
```
* **Theory:** Java-la direct-ah use panna mudiyatha sila ready-made tools-ah (libraries) veliyila irundhu import panrom. 
  - `Scanner`: User kitta irundhu keyboard input vangarathuku.
  - `Pattern` & `Matcher`: Text-la irundhu numbers-ah mattum filter panni edukura (Regex) tool-uku.

### B. Class and Main Method (Class-um Main Method-um)
```java
public class RtoFancyNumberChecker {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ...
    }
}
```
* **Class (RtoFancyNumberChecker):** Java-la ezhuthara ellaa code-um oru `class` kulla thaan irukanum. Ithu oru periya container or box maari.
* **Main Method (`public static void main`):** Computer unga program-ah run panna arambikkumpothu, **intha main method kulla iruka line-ah thaan mudhalla execute pannum**. Ithu thaan program-oda starting gate.

### C. Variables and Data Types (Mathippukal)
Code-la namma `String input` or `int val` nu use panniyirupom.
* **String:** Text characters (letters, symbols, spaces) store panna use aagum. E.g., `"MH12AB1234"`.
* **int:** Muzhu numbers (Integers) store panna use aagum. E.g., `786` or `1234`.

