## 4. Compiler vs Interpreter (Execution Theory)

Java program run aagurappo pinnadi nadakira background theory:

```mermaid
graph LR
    SourceCode["RtoFancyNumberChecker.java (Neenga ezhuthuna code)"] -->|Step 1: Javac Compiler| Bytecode["RtoFancyNumberChecker.class (Computer-ku puriyura Bytecode)"]
    Bytecode -->|Step 2: Java Virtual Machine JVM| Execution["Output: YES/NO (Terminal-la varum answer)"]
```

1. **Compilation (`javac`):** Human readable Java code-ah computer processor direct-ah purinjika mudiyathu. Athanala `javac` compiler vanthu unga code-ah bytecode (`.class` file) nu mathum.
2. **Execution (`java`):** Unga computer-la iruka **JVM (Java Virtual Machine)** intha bytecode-ah computer processor thagundha machine code-ah mathi real time output visual screen-la tharum.
